1
00:00:21,396 --> 00:00:24,691
We all live in manufactured realities.

2
00:00:25,525 --> 00:00:28,069
I look in the mirror,
I go, "Who the hell's that?"

3
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:32,949
We all follow some sort of script.

4
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:34,743
A little spritz?

5
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:37,954
I gotta look like we were working out
or something, you know?

6
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:44,669
All of us, in a way,
have a performative life.

7
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:48,423
As a father, uh, I am performative.

8
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:51,259
And in your own wedding,
you're performative.

9
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:53,011
And on and on and on.

10
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:56,639
And it's part of human nature,
of the human experience.

11
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,767
There's nothing wrong about it.

12
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,144
All right. Three, two…

13
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:04,064
You know something, maniacs?

14
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:07,942
I'm all pumped up
about Main Event karaoke tonight, brother.

15
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:10,028
I was walking down to meet you.

16
00:01:10,111 --> 00:01:11,071
Three, two, one.

17
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:12,781
Well, in case of Hulk Hogan,

18
00:01:12,864 --> 00:01:15,867
it would be interesting
to look into the performer

19
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:18,995
and into the real Hulk Hogan,

20
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:21,623
if he still exists.

21
00:01:21,706 --> 00:01:23,583
You know something, Hulkamaniacs?

22
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:28,254
I was all pumped up
about Hogan's Main Event karaoke tonight,

23
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:29,798
8:00 p.m. at Hogan's Hangout.

24
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:33,551
When I was strolling down the beach
in my banana hammock earlier today,

25
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:35,887
they were posing out in the parking lot.

26
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:38,014
They were posing on the beach.

27
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:43,895
Does he live the illusion himself
of being this character?

28
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:45,980
But let me tell you something, brother.

29
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:47,816
Hulkamania's still running wild.

30
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,859
Now you know what it's all about, brother.

31
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:51,653
So, what you gonna do?

32
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:53,488
When all my locals start singing

33
00:01:53,571 --> 00:01:57,575
and they tear the house down
just for you, brother?

34
00:01:58,451 --> 00:01:59,285
Sweet.

35
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:01,955
We have to know,
"Is there something authentic?"

36
00:02:02,038 --> 00:02:03,289
Something real?

37
00:02:03,373 --> 00:02:06,376
-Something truthful about it?
-Phew!

38
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,419
That was harder than the workout.

39
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:13,007
Okay. We'll see you guys down the road.
I'll call you in just a little while.

40
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:16,719
How much has he adopted the role

41
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:20,640
of Hulk Hogan in his own private life?

42
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:23,101
-Do you know his real name?
-Hulk Hogan?

43
00:02:23,184 --> 00:02:26,521
-Yeah.
-I don't even want to know his real name.

44
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:28,648
Keep it your secret.

45
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:44,330
It's an awesome shirt.
This thing's really smoking.

46
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,760
Drop your head back, Terry. Good.
Drop it down. Excellent.

47
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:02,307
I'll turn up the electricity on this side,
just let me know when.

48
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:04,976
That… That hip on that side hurts, doc.

49
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:11,191
At this point in your career,
you've done so much, and here you are.

50
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:13,776
Just to get out there
you gotta go through this.

51
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,862
And yet you keep doing it.

52
00:03:15,945 --> 00:03:18,489
You got to complete the circle, brother.
It's, uh…

53
00:03:20,658 --> 00:03:24,078
The job's not done yet, man.
You gotta… You gotta make sure.

54
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:28,458
This is an art form that, uh,
if you love it, it's in your blood.

55
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:31,753
I didn't get a pair of boots
from Santa for Christmas, you know.

56
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:35,548
Following WrestleMania X8,

57
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:39,093
Vince was back in love with Hulk Hogan.

58
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:42,764
It was like we're going to jump
back on the Hulk Hogan train.

59
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:47,185
And all of us were like, "No."
Like, "This is…" He got a nostalgia bump.

60
00:03:47,268 --> 00:03:50,230
"This thing will be dead in three weeks."

61
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:58,196
I actually should've quit back about '90.

62
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:01,616
I could've really ramped up
the movie stuff and the TV stuff.

63
00:04:02,283 --> 00:04:06,663
But instead, I kept going back again, so…

64
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:10,083
We can see Hogan feeding off the people,

65
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,793
feeding off Hulkamania.

66
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:18,758
Twenty, you know, thousand people roaring.

67
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:25,306
There's nothing like that.
You're walking that tightrope.

68
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:27,392
Hogan feeding off the Hulkamaniacs.

69
00:04:27,475 --> 00:04:29,894
This business is so tough to leave.

70
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,522
You know, they know I'm a step slower.

71
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:38,027
They know I'm on bonus time here,
and I love it.

72
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:40,196
And they respect that, you know.

73
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,198
I'm the last of a breed, you know.

74
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:46,411
And, uh, the respect they show me…

75
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:49,038
If I die, I hope I die out there.

76
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:55,920
Everybody says, "if you could do it
over again, would you?"

77
00:04:57,213 --> 00:04:58,464
I would change one thing.

78
00:04:58,548 --> 00:05:00,925
I started dropping the leg
when I was in Japan.

79
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:08,016
My arms used to be huge,
so why would you jump up and drop the leg

80
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,643
and land on your tailbone
every night for 40-plus years,

81
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:14,147
when you could use the sleeper hold
and not take any bumps?

82
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:17,567
One thing about this business,
no one leaves unscathed.

83
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:23,239
Every time Hulk Hogan did that leg drop,
compounding on his back, every time.

84
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:25,450
Here is a leg drop!

85
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:29,162
Those little small things,
over years, add up.

86
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:34,208
I kind of, like, kept rolling, you know?
But I wouldn't have been like this now.

87
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:36,419
I would've been
like a normal 70-year-old guy,

88
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:39,047
that I could walk around
and wouldn't be limping.

89
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:45,678
The back surgeries, the knee replacements,
shoulder replacements, hands, everything.

90
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:49,182
Supposed to get three epidurals a year.

91
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:52,477
I was getting three a week.

92
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:58,066
But, of course, that's the price you pay.

93
00:05:58,149 --> 00:06:00,943
It'd be different.
I'd be a completely different person.

94
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,695
You'd give up the other stuff?

95
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:03,946
No.

96
00:06:04,947 --> 00:06:05,948
Mm-hmm.

97
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,284
No.

98
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:10,620
-Yeah.
-Mm-hmm.

99
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:14,207
When you look
at Hulk Hogan, he went an extra lap.

100
00:06:17,293 --> 00:06:19,545
Hogan, at this stage in his career,
is incredibly limited.

101
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:22,382
He's old, uh, he's beat up.

102
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:26,094
Shawn Michaels got the hooks
here on Hulk Hogan.

103
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:30,556
Shawn Michaels was making fun
of how old I was and how beat-up I was.

104
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:33,393
"Getting old, brother."

105
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:36,062
I got news for you.
I'll be 102 years old, brother,

106
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:38,856
by the time I step into the ring
at SummerSlam.

107
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:42,985
And then for SummerSlam,
he went and oversold to make it a joke.

108
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,155
I'll show you.

109
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,786
It's on Shawn to make the match exciting.

110
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:58,042
Even if you're a giant Hulk Hogan fan,

111
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,086
you start to wonder
what he's still doing there.

112
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:03,923
A year later, I wrestled Randy Orton.

113
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:06,968
I had no idea that was gonna be
the last match in the WWE.

114
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:13,850
One, two, three!

115
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:28,197
You relied on your body
and performance for a long time.

116
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:31,909
Was that hard
to not be able to lean on that again?

117
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:33,578
Well, it's still hard, you know?

118
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:37,206
It's still hard
because you step back into the real world…

119
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:39,000
Hi.

120
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,878
Jeez, what a short night.

121
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:45,298
What did Santa Claus bring to you, huh?

122
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:46,966
What's up?

123
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:51,220
…you know, you have your highs
and your lows, and you have family issues.

124
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:54,974
And Linda was on her own there
for a long time.

125
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:57,518
That was his life.

126
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:01,814
He was out of the house
more than he was home.

127
00:08:02,523 --> 00:08:04,442
I'd been gone so much,

128
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:06,944
my family,

129
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:12,700
my marriage was already pretty much
in shambles already, at that point.

130
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:16,329
He'd just sit on the couch.
He liked to watch a lot of movies.

131
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:19,874
Just kind of quiet. He didn't like
to make a lot of conversation at dinner.

132
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:23,669
He really wasn't, like,
Mr. Personality at home anymore.

133
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:27,089
When you're a celebrity,
you belong to the public.

134
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,926
I'm like…
"Don't you have somewhere to be?"

135
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:32,053
We forgot cookies and milk.

136
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:34,138
We forgot Dad's present.

137
00:08:34,222 --> 00:08:35,640
Well, go get it.

138
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:37,475
Dad got a Segway.

139
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:45,191
I woke up one day, and I was an old man.
Didn't even know it happened.

140
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,362
I had missed the family unit.

141
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:52,281
The connection that me and Terry had.

142
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,453
I'd say, "Let's at least do something nice
as a family, with the kids."

143
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:00,998
Just have fun again.
Let's just do something as a family.

144
00:09:01,582 --> 00:09:02,625
Hi.

145
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:05,253
Look back at me, guys.

146
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:06,879
Or not.

147
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:14,262
And then one day, I got a call from VH1

148
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:16,847
about doing a reality show.

149
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:18,266
Linduce.

150
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:20,560
He called me Linduce,
which means "Little Linda."

151
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:24,897
We were all in the family room, he's like,
"Hey, I got a proposition for you guys."

152
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:28,401
"Do you guys wanna do a reality TV show?"

153
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:30,236
Of course the kids are like, "Yes!"

154
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:33,864
You know, because we saw The Osbournes
and Jessica Simpson,

155
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,616
and Brooke was all, you know, about that.

156
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,326
She's like, "Yeah, that would be cool!"

157
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:40,288
Oh my God, Mom. I'm going to cry.

158
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,123
Uh-oh, she's beginning to tear.

159
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:43,708
That was a pretty exciting thing.

160
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:46,127
-Mom, where did you get this?
-It's so awesome.

161
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,920
I think it was exciting for Terry.

162
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:48,838
Yeah!

163
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,923
He wanted that platform.

164
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:56,929
I explained to Linda that my prayer was
that it would bring Linda and I together

165
00:09:57,013 --> 00:10:00,558
on some form or another,
to have something in common,

166
00:10:00,641 --> 00:10:03,936
where we could, you know, be excited
about something and move forward.

167
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:07,732
We're in business.

168
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:11,402
Fuck it, all right, I'm down with that.
Yeah, let's do it.

169
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:14,447
I can't believe my dad said yes.
I'm just praying to God.

170
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:17,283
Please don't let me wake up.
Please don't let it be a dream.

171
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:21,287
Brooke always wanted to be a singer.
She wanted to be the next Britney Spears.

172
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:24,790
He was like, "They want
to make it like a stage-dad thing."

173
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,292
-Is that okay?
-That works for me.

174
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,209
Yay!

175
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,587
Hogan Knows Best.

176
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:34,967
To help Brooke with her singing career,
to help Nick establish himself, you know.

177
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,387
So he wouldn't have to be
called Nick Hogan, or Brooke Hogan.

178
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:41,140
They could be the Bolleas
and have their own career.

179
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,267
You know, I think Linda…

180
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,895
Let's see, let me work my camera here.

181
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:49,231
…always wanted to be in front
of the camera instead of behind.

182
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:50,358
Okay, cut.

183
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:56,322
I said,
"Some of the things that are gonna happen,

184
00:10:56,405 --> 00:11:00,201
you'll be thrown into the celebrity world
if the show does good,

185
00:11:00,284 --> 00:11:02,662
and life as you know it
will cease to exist."

186
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:04,705
It's the calm before the storm.

187
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:11,128
Like he said, "Make sure you guys fully
are aware of what we're getting into."

188
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:13,089
And I said, "Hey, I'm down. Let's go."

189
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:18,427
Uh-oh. Terry as Hulk!

190
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:20,137
Where is everybody?

191
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:25,601
Hogan Knows Best.

192
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:31,857
-She is really dangerous.
-Pull it out!

193
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:35,444
There was two months
of having black all over our windows

194
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:37,405
and people running through the house.

195
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:40,116
A big crew, like, 28 people in the crew.

196
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:44,370
Eventually, we took the kids out of school
because it was just too much time.

197
00:11:44,453 --> 00:11:46,038
Oh ah oh

198
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:50,918
They took the credit
For your second symphony

199
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,962
Rewritten by machine
On new technology…

200
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:55,756
I realized, "Oh my God, I'm a celebrity."

201
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:58,926
I'm always used
to getting that with my dad.

202
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:00,219
It's weird for him

203
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:03,681
to have gone through his whole life
being the icon that he has become.

204
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:06,559
It's happening for my kids.

205
00:12:06,642 --> 00:12:08,519
People are asking me for my autograph.

206
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:12,732
We thought it was a really cool thing
for all of us to be a part of

207
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:16,652
because this was kind of the first thing
for us as a family to participate in.

208
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:18,946
Terry loved it. We all loved that show.

209
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:23,701
If Hulkamaniacs knew
I was getting my hair straightened

210
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:26,328
using a pink brush,
Hulkamania would be over.

211
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,247
…and it seems so long ago

212
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:30,249
VH1 was very, very excited.

213
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:33,586
They were just stoked.
The numbers went through the roof.

214
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:36,172
Your show did phenomenally last season,

215
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:38,924
and now you're back
for a second season of Hogan…

216
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:43,345
Video killed the radio star
Video killed the radio star…

217
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:46,682
I know it was a huge upside
to helping Brooke's music career.

218
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:49,059
She was so close to really making it.

219
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:52,688
We thought this would tip the scales
and really get her out there.

220
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:56,442
It didn't really do anything for Nick

221
00:12:56,525 --> 00:13:00,112
except paint him in the corner
as a Dennis the Menace-type kid.

222
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:04,200
They'd film me
doing these 12-year-old antics

223
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:05,993
when really I was, like, 16,

224
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:09,872
and I was going to, you know,
work on a car with my friends

225
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:10,873
or produce music.

226
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:13,501
If the day was a little slow, "Hey, Nick,

227
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:16,462
go fill some water balloons up
and go throw them at people."

228
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:20,007
And next thing you know,
the cops grab Nick.

229
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:24,887
Look, dude, I busted my ass to get it,
so we could be comfortable around here,

230
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:27,014
and you're spending money like it's water.

231
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:30,976
-I love you. Thanks for doing good.
-All right. That was really nice of you.

232
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,813
It's tough as a parent
to see your kids grow up.

233
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:35,064
It seems like it was yesterday

234
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:38,442
when they were just hanging out
at the beach and pool with us

235
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:40,611
and drinking chocolate bottles.

236
00:13:40,694 --> 00:13:45,366
I was working so much the last 15 years
I've missed the whole enchilada.

237
00:13:45,449 --> 00:13:47,576
They showed the soft side of Hulk.

238
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:52,248
He just has a good heart,
and I love that about him.

239
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:55,125
And he was good with the kids like that.

240
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:59,338
Are you listening?
No kissing. This is serious.

241
00:13:59,421 --> 00:14:01,549
The really great stuff was the fact that,

242
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:06,804
"Oh my gosh, he's a father and a husband.
He's got problems with the wife."

243
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,889
-What's up?
-"He's just like us."

244
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,809
I know what boys are thinking about,
and I was one.

245
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:15,729
And the boys' hormones are going crazy,
and all they can think about is sex.

246
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:17,940
The audience changed.

247
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:21,902
They became a huge female demo
that was attracted to Hulk Hogan

248
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,863
because I was a father and a husband.

249
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:25,781
Is that a miniskirt?

250
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,366
-Yeah.
-Mm.

251
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:29,952
Think miniskirts are good
to ride on roller coasters?

252
00:14:30,035 --> 00:14:32,162
-How old's Adam?
-Just turned 22.

253
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:33,664
22?

254
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:37,626
They kind of made things lighter than,
"Hey, let me tell you something, brother."

255
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,420
That screaming maniac.

256
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:43,507
The version that you saw
of Terry was, in my opinion, Terry.

257
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:44,758
It was what I lived with.

258
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:47,720
It was the guy that was not
in the red and yellow boots,

259
00:14:47,803 --> 00:14:50,097
not putting on a performance
for the people.

260
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:54,727
They realized that Hulk Hogan was Terry,
and I was a normal dad and normal person.

261
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:57,980
So there was a lot of good things
that came with that,

262
00:14:58,063 --> 00:15:01,734
but also, you know,
the mistakes and the disagreements

263
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:07,072
and the drama of trying to live life,
you know, shone through.

264
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:09,408
To 22.

265
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:11,619
-Still with you.
-And you.

266
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:14,538
-That's because I love you.
-Mm. I love you too.

267
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:16,832
I would marry you again
if you asked me to.

268
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,751
-Would you marry me again?
-Mm-hmm.

269
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:20,085
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

270
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:23,088
-Would you sign a prenup?
-What would you put in?

271
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:25,966
-I don't know. There's no reason for it.
-See? I know.

272
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:30,137
If you divorce me, I'll kill you.
It doesn't matter.

273
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,096
Wow.

274
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:35,017
Being together 24 hours a day,
seven days a week,

275
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:39,396
the reality show Hogan Knows Best
was kind of like a recipe for disaster.

276
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,857
-I'm scared!
-Everybody's got that same attitude.

277
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,567
-I'm tired of it.
-No, I don't.

278
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:44,985
So where was I?

279
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:47,321
Right where you started, nowhere.

280
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:51,533
Having your personal problems
with your family

281
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:56,622
being aired for public consumption
caused all kinds of turmoil.

282
00:15:56,705 --> 00:16:02,169
Yo, Linda! How many times have I told you
I don't want the maid in my closet?

283
00:16:02,252 --> 00:16:05,005
Whatever. Why don't you put stuff back
when you're done?

284
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:06,507
I'm so sick of this.

285
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:12,972
It put everyone, as a family,
in a very intense situation.

286
00:16:14,264 --> 00:16:18,227
And then when real issues
start to come up,

287
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:23,232
you don't really have time to address them
the way that you naturally would.

288
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:25,484
-We could use the money.
-You could always use the money.

289
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:27,945
No matter how much money I make,
it still isn't enough.

290
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:33,659
You know, I would,
you know, come home with a check,

291
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:36,036
a seven-digit check, and hand it to her,

292
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,998
and she'd throw it back in my face,
"Was that all you got?"

293
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:41,667
It wasn't the old Linda,
the happy one, you know?

294
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:44,545
It was definitely a different person.

295
00:16:44,628 --> 00:16:47,840
Toward the last season, things were weird.

296
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:50,384
He wasn't my soulmate.

297
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:55,180
I want to thank the master of the universe
for agreeing to let me come along.

298
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:57,182
-Welcome.
-After she changed her mind.

299
00:16:57,266 --> 00:17:00,602
And she said didn't want to be around me.
So thank you very much.

300
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:03,313
I just remember not even being there.

301
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:07,526
I was just going through so much stress
with my family, and it was just so insane.

302
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:11,321
I think when you have fame
and go through struggles and hard times,

303
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:14,324
it's almost like a higher rise
and a harder fall, you know?

304
00:17:16,118 --> 00:17:20,831
Toward the end, it was like,
"Uh… No more cameras, I need a break."

305
00:17:20,914 --> 00:17:24,585
It'd take me about two seconds
to pack up my friggin' closet and be gone.

306
00:17:24,668 --> 00:17:25,836
-Again?
-Yeah.

307
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:27,463
-Again?
-For good.

308
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,506
When we went
into the couples' therapy, you know,

309
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:31,842
that was all kind of, like, real.

310
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:35,012
Some of our arguments have been
so intense Linda verbally suggested,

311
00:17:35,095 --> 00:17:38,057
"Maybe we should go our separate ways,
or maybe get a lawyer,

312
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,850
and maybe we should just be divorced."

313
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,311
-So the words were spoken?
-Yeah.

314
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:45,814
Are you nervous
about your parents getting a divorce?

315
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,483
-No.
-No, and even if it did--

316
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:50,027
It's not going to happen.
They love hard, fight hard.

317
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:52,821
-They're too scared.
-I wanna hear what Nick's gotta say.

318
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:55,115
I'm not… I'm not worried.
I don't think it'll happen.

319
00:17:55,199 --> 00:17:57,743
But even if it did,
I mean, we're so close,

320
00:17:57,826 --> 00:17:59,870
I think
that we'd all stick together anyways.

321
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:02,498
Are you 100%, in your mind,
out of this marriage?

322
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:03,540
-Who, me?
-Yeah.

323
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:04,833
No, I'm not out at all.

324
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:07,002
When will you be out, if this continues?

325
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,379
I'll probably be dead when it's over.

326
00:18:10,964 --> 00:18:15,886
I always thought that, you know,
it could be fixed for better or worse.

327
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:17,387
I needed to hang in there.

328
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:21,225
"I really don't understand at all
how we got here,

329
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:24,019
why we love so much and still might fail."

330
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:28,190
"Out of touch, out of love
And out of place"

331
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:32,236
"Losing you would be like living
Without ever seeing my children's face"

332
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:35,405
"I stand here before you, and…"

333
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:42,287
Everything is just ripped, wasted.

334
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,581
It is definitely a mess.

335
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:47,918
It's just going to take forever
to clean everything up.

336
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,963
I do know that he loved me.
I know that he loved me. I know.

337
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:53,465
I know that he did,
and he was crazy about me.

338
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:55,884
"Because being in love with you,

339
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:59,972
only if for a second,
means I'll never live to regret it."

340
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:08,147
He was hiding something.

341
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:11,233
He just wasn't acting like himself,
and I knew something was up.

342
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:14,778
My housekeeper came to me,
and she said, "Is this yours?"

343
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:17,322
And it was a little gold hoop.
I was like, "No."

344
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:21,451
And I go, "Where was it? In my bathroom?
Where was it?" She goes, "In your bed."

345
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:23,495
Hulk Hogan's daughter

346
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:26,331
might want
to run her father over with a tank

347
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:29,877
after he reportedly slept, get this,
with one of her close friends.

348
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:33,797
She was a person I was dating
who was part of the record company,

349
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,632
almost like a chaperone for Brooke.

350
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:38,177
Brooke Hogan says
her friend started having whoopie

351
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:41,763
with the huckster in 2006,
while he was still married to her mother.

352
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,182
I'm out of here.

353
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:53,233
I was with him from the time I was 22
to the time I was 49 years old.

354
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,574
And that's half of your life.

355
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:01,491
Ugh!

356
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:06,914
I didn't know, you know,
why he cheated on me.

357
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,625
I'm kind of scared to be out here.
I really shouldn't be.

358
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:12,252
And I just felt like a complete failure.

359
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:14,630
But you get to that point where

360
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:19,468
you're not really sad anymore,
you're just kind of more mad.

361
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:22,012
You're in self-survival mode now.

362
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:26,975
I came back from wrestling,
from Germany, one time,

363
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,436
and the house was completely cleaned out.

364
00:20:29,519 --> 00:20:33,649
Safes were ripped out of the wall.
Everything was gone except my clothes.

365
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:42,658
It's hard to have your skeletons,
you know, pulled out of your closet

366
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:44,826
and just waved
in front of everybody's face,

367
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,328
and humiliated in the world,

368
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,622
and our family
would go through all this stuff.

369
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:53,210
Coming and going from
the courthouse for their bitter divorce,

370
00:20:53,293 --> 00:20:55,462
the Hogan's rarely shy away from cameras.

371
00:20:58,507 --> 00:21:01,969
That's not the same person I married.
She's… We pray for her every night.

372
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:03,136
It was terrible.

373
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,889
It was a very, very tough time.

374
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:09,851
It was to the point where we didn't speak
to each other anymore. At all.

375
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:12,521
And so everything
had to go through lawyers.

376
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:14,314
Listen to me, Mr. Bollea.

377
00:21:14,398 --> 00:21:18,026
Mr. Bollea. Mr. Bollea.
Are you going to wrestle with me here?

378
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:22,114
Are you going to come across the cameras?
You had your time to talk. You're done.

379
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:24,700
You are the person
that has caused this issue.

380
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:28,203
It made it incredibly difficult
for the kids.

381
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,831
I tried to call the kids
for two months and couldn't get them.

382
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:32,124
Nobody'd even answer.

383
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:37,462
I don't know if I really want
to get into this stuff for this.

384
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:39,089
I just… I don't know.

385
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:41,300
Hogan's lawyers say the 40,000 a month

386
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:43,969
Linda is currently getting in alimony
is too much,

387
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:45,929
and they want that amount reduced.

388
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:48,307
They brought a slew of witnesses
to the stand

389
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,977
to try and prove
Linda is blowing all her money on drugs,

390
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:55,230
fancy clothes,
and her much younger boyfriend.

391
00:21:56,231 --> 00:22:01,570
She was, you know, bouncing around,
flying all over with her boyfriend.

392
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:05,949
Who actually went to school
with Nick and Brooke.

393
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:08,702
We were talking.
I asked how old he was. He said he was 25.

394
00:22:08,785 --> 00:22:11,455
I was like, "Oh, okay, fine, great."

395
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:14,791
He was young, but what the heck, you know?
Let's go have a margarita.

396
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:17,919
We dated, I don't know,
for like a couple weeks,

397
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,630
and we went somewhere,
and I was like, "Do you want beer?"

398
00:22:20,714 --> 00:22:24,009
And he's like,
"I'm not really 21, and I'm not 25."

399
00:22:24,092 --> 00:22:27,137
I go… Now I really have fallen
for this guy.

400
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:30,265
I'm like, "Well, how old are you?"
He goes, "I'm 19."

401
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,101
"Are you not lying about that?"

402
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:36,229
"Because if you're lying about that,
we've got problems, you know?"

403
00:22:37,272 --> 00:22:40,942
The judge wouldn't let me live
in my big house or my little house,

404
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:42,819
so I had nowhere to go.

405
00:22:44,237 --> 00:22:46,073
I rented an apartment.

406
00:22:46,156 --> 00:22:49,534
It was in the top of this building
where I could see down the beach,

407
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:51,661
where I could see my beach house.

408
00:22:51,745 --> 00:22:55,290
It was tough because I could hear
my cigarette boat start up in the morning,

409
00:22:55,374 --> 00:22:57,793
and Linda's 18-year-old boyfriend
would back it out.

410
00:22:57,876 --> 00:22:59,961
Well, I see something so cute.

411
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:02,547
It is a gorgeous day.

412
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:05,675
I thought, he won't know how it feels
until he sees it happen to me.

413
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:08,053
He'd come by me
and stop where my apartment was.

414
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:10,055
He'd sit in my boat and smoke a joint.

415
00:23:10,138 --> 00:23:13,433
And I'd go, "That's Terry.
Drive by, go in close, go in close."

416
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:17,854
You know, I was making all over Charlie,
and, you know, just driving in circles.

417
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:22,776
I was like, "See? How do you feel
about that? It hurts, right? Ouch."

418
00:23:23,443 --> 00:23:27,197
And I didn't mean to be such a catty…
You know, rub it in.

419
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:30,242
But I thought,
"A little bit wouldn't hurt."

420
00:23:31,368 --> 00:23:33,161
It was, like, thrown in my face big time.

421
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:35,747
I'd have trouble with a guy
30 years younger than me

422
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:38,458
because I'm afraid he's going
to yell out, "Mommy," during sex.

423
00:23:40,293 --> 00:23:42,504
-You know?
-Is that so wrong? No, just kidding.

424
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:44,172
I… I'd had it.

425
00:23:46,007 --> 00:23:47,926
It's as bizarre as it is shocking.

426
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:50,971
Hulk Hogan in the middle
of a bitter divorce,

427
00:23:51,054 --> 00:23:54,683
telling Rolling Stone
he now understands O.J. Simpson.

428
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:58,145
The magazine says Hogan is so bitter
he sounded homicidal,

429
00:23:58,228 --> 00:24:02,399
saying, quote, "I could have turned
everything into a crime scene like O.J.,

430
00:24:02,482 --> 00:24:04,484
cutting everybody's throat."

431
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:07,654
But Hogan says the quote
is taken out of context.

432
00:24:08,238 --> 00:24:11,658
I spent three days
with Rolling Stone, you know?

433
00:24:11,741 --> 00:24:13,243
I thought the guy was my friend.

434
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:16,163
He warmed up to me,
we became buddies, you know,

435
00:24:16,246 --> 00:24:17,789
and all of a sudden, you know,

436
00:24:17,873 --> 00:24:21,460
we're sitting on my back porch
and drinking beer on the beach

437
00:24:21,543 --> 00:24:24,296
and had a little buzz on,
and he asked me about O.J. Simpson.

438
00:24:25,464 --> 00:24:30,802
I said, "Wow, brother, you know,
I've been that jealous and mad at a girl

439
00:24:30,886 --> 00:24:33,805
that I completely understand
how he flipped out."

440
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:37,809
Of course, there's that male instinct
that you'd love to get him in the ring.

441
00:24:37,893 --> 00:24:41,563
I could've been like O.J. Simpson,
but I chose not to.

442
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:45,317
But I would never do that.
I would never go there.

443
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,903
I wish I'd never done the interview
with Rolling Stone.

444
00:24:47,986 --> 00:24:51,323
His wife's attorney says Linda
canceled her flight home to Clearwater

445
00:24:51,406 --> 00:24:52,866
and is now in hiding.

446
00:24:52,949 --> 00:24:55,327
And it's terrifying to my client.

447
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:56,995
-You heard what he said?
-Yeah.

448
00:24:57,078 --> 00:24:59,289
About how he understands
what O.J. was feeling?

449
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:02,250
You know, I'm happy
because I'm 5,000 miles away from him.

450
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:07,005
I went home, and I… I… I started drinking

451
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:10,675
and, uh, you know, started eating pills.

452
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:13,386
And I just went down this rabbit hole
for a couple of days,

453
00:25:13,470 --> 00:25:16,389
and the next thing I know
I'm in front of my bathroom

454
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:21,061
with a gun in my mouth, and, um…

455
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:24,856
not knowing what I was doing,
you know.

456
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:29,402
He was down, and he was hurting,

457
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:33,823
and I was probably
not the only person he could talk to,

458
00:25:33,907 --> 00:25:38,078
but one of the ones he felt
most comfortable talking to at that time.

459
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:40,664
And I told my wife, I said,

460
00:25:40,747 --> 00:25:44,709
"I think I'm going to go to Florida
for a while and just hang out."

461
00:25:44,793 --> 00:25:47,879
She said, "When are you coming back?"
I said, "I don't know."

462
00:25:54,803 --> 00:25:57,556
He was in the darkest,
most devastating part of his life

463
00:25:57,639 --> 00:25:58,515
up to that point.

464
00:25:59,516 --> 00:26:01,059
Your wife's divorcing you,

465
00:26:01,142 --> 00:26:05,355
and your doctor's giving you
fistfuls of pills that would kill a horse,

466
00:26:05,438 --> 00:26:08,608
and you're chasing it down
with a quart of vodka a day.

467
00:26:08,692 --> 00:26:10,527
I hit rock bottom.

468
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:13,238
I gave Linda 70% of everything

469
00:26:13,321 --> 00:26:16,575
because I just didn't want
to ever talk to her again, be with her.

470
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:19,619
I never wanted to see her again.
I gave her everything to get rid of her.

471
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:25,667
And after the divorce, I… I had no money.

472
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:29,004
I was broke.

473
00:26:30,755 --> 00:26:32,632
And so TNA saved me.

474
00:26:32,716 --> 00:26:34,718
Hogan! Hogan! Hogan!

475
00:26:34,801 --> 00:26:37,304
Hey, maniacs,
I can't hear you guys out there.

476
00:26:37,387 --> 00:26:39,639
There is no single name

477
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:43,143
that defines an industry
more than Hulk Hogan.

478
00:26:43,226 --> 00:26:46,271
The man, the brand, all you Hulkamaniacs.

479
00:26:46,354 --> 00:26:48,440
Hogan! Hogan!

480
00:26:48,523 --> 00:26:51,693
TNA was a deal
that I put together for him.

481
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:57,449
Hulk was reluctant to go,
but he needed the money.

482
00:26:59,075 --> 00:27:00,285
TNA!

483
00:27:00,368 --> 00:27:02,996
TNA formed after the death of WCW.

484
00:27:03,079 --> 00:27:06,791
It was maybe a gnat that was
kind of annoying around the face of WWE.

485
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:10,253
It wasn't competitive
on a financial scale in any way,

486
00:27:10,337 --> 00:27:12,005
but it was a place for guys to work.

487
00:27:12,088 --> 00:27:14,215
TNA! TNA! TNA!

488
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:17,927
What's up, TNA maniacs?

489
00:27:18,595 --> 00:27:22,724
When he first came in,
he was an attraction, a figurehead.

490
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:27,437
Immediately, people will want to tune in
just to see what Hulk Hogan is gonna do.

491
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:31,232
This is TNA's reckoning day, brother.

492
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:36,279
The idea was he'll wrestle
and be an active member of the roster.

493
00:27:37,072 --> 00:27:40,784
But it became very apparent very quickly
he was in no shape to do that.

494
00:27:49,125 --> 00:27:51,711
My body just had had enough.

495
00:27:53,922 --> 00:27:56,466
In the emergency room here.

496
00:27:57,592 --> 00:28:03,890
About 3:00 in the morning,
my back, uh, went into this major spasm.

497
00:28:04,808 --> 00:28:08,937
There were a couple of hip replacements,
a couple of knee replacements.

498
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:13,942
As the surgeries started mounting up,
I couldn't sleep in my bed.

499
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:16,778
I had to sleep in a chair, you know.

500
00:28:16,861 --> 00:28:20,240
And if I just…
If i just twitched my finger like that,

501
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:21,908
my whole back would spasm and torque.

502
00:28:21,991 --> 00:28:26,413
The spine should look like this.

503
00:28:28,623 --> 00:28:30,041
And this is your back.

504
00:28:30,792 --> 00:28:33,586
-So you can't turn right now, you know.
-Oh my God!

505
00:28:34,504 --> 00:28:38,007
After back surgery number three,
you know, I can't walk.

506
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:41,094
Surgery number four, I go back in.

507
00:28:41,177 --> 00:28:44,472
Surgery number five, I go back in.
Surgery number six…

508
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:46,850
Really getting over this crap.

509
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:50,562
Time to come back and take over.

510
00:28:50,645 --> 00:28:53,898
I talked to E.
He said everything was cool with TNA.

511
00:28:55,191 --> 00:28:56,693
It was hard to see.

512
00:28:56,776 --> 00:29:01,698
There were times when I felt really shitty
about myself for making him do it.

513
00:29:02,657 --> 00:29:07,203
He wasn't doing basics of pro wrestling.
All he could do was bleed.

514
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:09,372
That is that weapon.

515
00:29:09,456 --> 00:29:12,041
There's obviously
a physical limitation to everything,

516
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:15,420
and he showed us those limits
in the ring in TNA.

517
00:29:15,503 --> 00:29:16,796
Oh my God.

518
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:19,841
Doctors said,
"Oh, you need a spinal cord stimulator."

519
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:21,676
Okay, what is that?

520
00:29:23,052 --> 00:29:25,221
They said,
"It's a battery we'll put in your back,

521
00:29:25,305 --> 00:29:28,308
and you have a portable,
like a TV clicker in your hand,

522
00:29:28,391 --> 00:29:29,893
and every time there's any pain,

523
00:29:29,976 --> 00:29:33,897
it shoots an electronic signal
to your head, and it blocks the pain."

524
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:35,398
It gives you a jolt of electricity.

525
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:39,611
His back was in so much pain,

526
00:29:39,694 --> 00:29:43,406
I would literally have to go to his hotel
and help him get out of bed

527
00:29:43,490 --> 00:29:46,951
to get into the shower
to get ready to go to the shoot.

528
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:50,205
He was contractually obligated to do it,
and he wanted to do it.

529
00:29:50,955 --> 00:29:53,374
I was taking 80-milligram fentanyls.

530
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:56,461
Two in the morning,
stuffin' them under my gums here.

531
00:29:56,544 --> 00:30:01,341
I had two 300-milligram patches
of fentanyl on my legs,

532
00:30:01,424 --> 00:30:06,679
and they gave me six 1,500-milligram
fentanyl lollipops to eat.

533
00:30:06,763 --> 00:30:09,641
I went to the pharmacy.
He goes, "You should be dead."

534
00:30:09,724 --> 00:30:12,977
"We have never seen a human being
take this much fentanyl."

535
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:17,607
But he was in so much freaking pain.

536
00:30:19,108 --> 00:30:20,860
Is it possible for any wrestler

537
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:22,654
to have a graceful ending to their career?

538
00:30:22,737 --> 00:30:25,240
-Doesn't seem like it, does it?
-Doesn't seem so.

539
00:30:28,993 --> 00:30:30,954
We were in a room together, about to film.

540
00:30:31,037 --> 00:30:33,248
He says,
"Hold on, I gotta take this call."

541
00:30:33,331 --> 00:30:35,708
And I'm sitting five feet from him.

542
00:30:36,376 --> 00:30:38,920
"Yep. Okay."

543
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:43,466
Silence. "Okay." Hangs up the phone.

544
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:47,971
And he looks down at his phone,
and he looks up at me, and he says,

545
00:30:48,054 --> 00:30:52,308
"I just found out there's going to be
a sex tape coming out, and I'm in it."

546
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:53,935
Hulk Hogan has been described

547
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:56,688
as the most recognized
wrestling star worldwide,

548
00:30:56,771 --> 00:30:59,315
but the international superstar,
born Terry Bollea,

549
00:30:59,399 --> 00:31:01,943
was recently seen by millions
in a different light

550
00:31:02,026 --> 00:31:04,320
after a tape that he claims
was secretly recorded

551
00:31:04,404 --> 00:31:08,449
was shared by the popular
online media company Gawker.

552
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:12,912
And his legal counsel demanded repeatedly

553
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:15,874
that Gawker remove that video
from its website.

554
00:31:15,957 --> 00:31:18,251
Gawker refused to do so.

555
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:23,590
-Yeah.
-Feel good? Feel comfy?

556
00:31:23,673 --> 00:31:26,175
Hold on one second.
I got to do one thing. Ah!

557
00:31:28,595 --> 00:31:32,181
New Zealand. New Zealand. New Zealand.

558
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:34,767
Mah-mah-mah-mah-mah-mah.
Mah-mah-mah-mah.

559
00:31:34,851 --> 00:31:36,436
-Okay.
-Okay.

560
00:31:36,519 --> 00:31:38,104
All right. Who are you?

561
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:41,107
My name's Ken Turkel.
I'm a trial attorney in Tampa, Florida,

562
00:31:41,190 --> 00:31:43,484
and I represented Hulk Hogan
in the Gawker lawsuit.

563
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:49,240
Gawker was a media company
that had made its bones,

564
00:31:49,324 --> 00:31:51,993
essentially, violating
people's privacy rights,

565
00:31:52,076 --> 00:31:53,369
following people.

566
00:31:53,453 --> 00:31:55,580
You know,
they had a thing called Gawker Stalker

567
00:31:55,663 --> 00:32:00,376
where they would find celebrities out
and take pictures and post them.

568
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:06,674
But this was a surreptitious recording
of Terry, of Hulk, in a private act,

569
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:09,135
in a private bedroom
at his best friend's house.

570
00:32:09,218 --> 00:32:10,720
Hogan is suing the website

571
00:32:10,803 --> 00:32:15,183
for posting a tape of him
with the wife of his then-best friend.

572
00:32:15,266 --> 00:32:18,019
And Terry simply asked
for Gawker to take it down.

573
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:20,521
They refused to take the video down.

574
00:32:20,605 --> 00:32:21,731
Gawker's argument was

575
00:32:21,814 --> 00:32:25,109
that it was protected
by the First Amendment as newsworthy.

576
00:32:25,193 --> 00:32:27,654
When they hit the go button,
there was nowhere to hide.

577
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:30,281
You know, and now, Terry Bollea, the man,

578
00:32:30,365 --> 00:32:34,118
wasn't allowed my privacy
behind closed doors.

579
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:37,038
And, you know, that's pretty much it.

580
00:32:37,121 --> 00:32:39,207
There were a bunch of people in the media

581
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:43,169
who saw it as like, "Oh, you know,
look at these First Amendment champions,

582
00:32:43,252 --> 00:32:46,422
and how dare we interrupt the discourse
and dialog of America."

583
00:32:46,506 --> 00:32:48,049
We weren't doing that, man.

584
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:52,720
This was shitty under any, any evaluation,
what they did here.

585
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:56,057
Gawker's attorney suggested
the tape was a publicity stunt,

586
00:32:56,140 --> 00:32:59,185
but the pro wrestler laments
it was devastating

587
00:32:59,268 --> 00:33:01,813
to his personal and professional life.

588
00:33:01,896 --> 00:33:04,440
It was at a really low point in my life,

589
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:09,237
when I was in the previous marriage,
when things were bottomed out completely,

590
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:13,032
and I was with some friends,
and I made a wrong choice.

591
00:33:13,116 --> 00:33:18,830
And now, all of a sudden, it surfaces,
you know, over six years later.

592
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:21,165
He was horrified at the idea

593
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:24,377
of a little kid googling him
and seeing that.

594
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,796
Genuinely horrified at it.

595
00:33:26,879 --> 00:33:29,090
I was completely humiliated.

596
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:31,718
The kids can't separate the character
from the real person.

597
00:33:31,801 --> 00:33:33,302
Let's start with the person.

598
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:36,472
Well, the person is sitting here today
under oath as Terry Bollea.

599
00:33:36,556 --> 00:33:40,268
Now, as the character,
I've body-slammed elephants,

600
00:33:40,351 --> 00:33:42,854
you know, I've surfed on tiger sharks.

601
00:33:42,937 --> 00:33:47,442
The only similarities to me are
I wear a bandana on my head as Hulk Hogan,

602
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:51,404
and sometimes I wear a bandana
as Terry Bollea.

603
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:54,657
I think for the first time
in probably 30 years,

604
00:33:54,741 --> 00:33:57,702
the Gawker trial
actually forced Hulk Hogan

605
00:33:57,785 --> 00:34:01,664
to think about the difference
between Terry Bollea and Hulk Hogan.

606
00:34:01,748 --> 00:34:04,500
The mailman, they don't go, "Hey, Terry."
They go, "Hey, Hulk."

607
00:34:04,584 --> 00:34:07,545
So I have to go, "What's up, brother?"
Give him a little edge.

608
00:34:07,628 --> 00:34:09,756
Happy turkey leg, brother.

609
00:34:10,798 --> 00:34:16,095
It really makes me realize
the only safe place is in the house.

610
00:34:16,179 --> 00:34:17,764
I don't know of anyone

611
00:34:17,847 --> 00:34:19,974
who had less privacy
than Terry Bollea did.

612
00:34:20,058 --> 00:34:22,560
By being a big celebrity, if anything,

613
00:34:22,643 --> 00:34:24,645
in those places
where you deserve your privacy,

614
00:34:24,729 --> 00:34:27,732
it's actually that much more sacred.

615
00:34:27,815 --> 00:34:30,610
That's the entire point of our case.

616
00:34:32,487 --> 00:34:35,031
An expert
claiming Gawker made millions of dollars

617
00:34:35,114 --> 00:34:36,365
when it published the tape,

618
00:34:36,449 --> 00:34:43,164
so now a Pinellas County jury says
Gawker should pay Hogan $140 million.

619
00:34:44,832 --> 00:34:48,711
He wanted to send a message back out
that, like, "Look, this was wrong."

620
00:34:48,795 --> 00:34:51,589
And he wanted to get
his integrity back from this.

621
00:34:51,672 --> 00:34:55,760
I think we made history today
because, uh, we protected a lot of people

622
00:34:55,843 --> 00:34:58,679
from maybe going through
what I went through,

623
00:34:58,763 --> 00:35:00,848
so we're very excited and very happy.

624
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:04,852
So during the Gawker trial,
he wins a giant verdict.

625
00:35:04,936 --> 00:35:08,773
But then the transcripts
of the tape came out.

626
00:35:08,856 --> 00:35:10,858
It's what we haven't heard on that tape,

627
00:35:10,942 --> 00:35:14,612
a racial slur, that has caused
the Hulkster the most disgrace.

628
00:35:14,695 --> 00:35:18,908
A very strong man learned
today that his own words can hurt him,

629
00:35:18,991 --> 00:35:22,161
Bollea reportedly uses racial slurs.

630
00:35:24,288 --> 00:35:28,668
I'm a person that got very mad
about a personal situation. I used a word.

631
00:35:30,169 --> 00:35:34,090
Yeah, I regret it,
because even under that heavy, crazy fire,

632
00:35:34,173 --> 00:35:38,261
I should have remained still
and kept my mouth shut.

633
00:35:38,344 --> 00:35:41,848
But what I said resonates
and has an echo effect.

634
00:35:41,931 --> 00:35:44,142
It keeps vibrating for years.

635
00:35:44,225 --> 00:35:45,852
He released a statement saying,

636
00:35:45,935 --> 00:35:49,063
"It was unacceptable for me
to have used that offensive language."

637
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:53,234
"There is no excuse for it,
and I apologize for having done it."

638
00:35:54,193 --> 00:35:56,445
I've driven the car.
I keep hitting the wall,

639
00:35:56,529 --> 00:36:00,992
crashing and burning,
saying stupid stuff and messing up.

640
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:02,827
Whenever I say I have regrets,

641
00:36:02,910 --> 00:36:06,873
it's because
I didn't man up when I said it.

642
00:36:08,374 --> 00:36:12,879
I never should have said what I said.
It was wrong. I'm embarrassed by it.

643
00:36:12,962 --> 00:36:15,423
But a lot of people need to realize

644
00:36:15,506 --> 00:36:17,925
that you inherit things
from your environment.

645
00:36:20,887 --> 00:36:23,139
At that point,
there was still a relationship,

646
00:36:23,222 --> 00:36:26,267
business-wise, between Hulk Hogan and WWE.

647
00:36:26,350 --> 00:36:31,189
So when all the stuff came out,
I'm the guy that had to call and say,

648
00:36:31,272 --> 00:36:34,775
"Yeah, we can't move forward here, Terry,
so, you know, we're done."

649
00:36:36,527 --> 00:36:38,404
The WWE saying in a statement,

650
00:36:38,487 --> 00:36:41,490
"We are committed
to embracing and celebrating

651
00:36:41,574 --> 00:36:43,993
individuals from all backgrounds."

652
00:36:44,076 --> 00:36:47,455
Your image, your likeness,
your name erased.

653
00:36:47,538 --> 00:36:48,915
Yeah, like I never existed.

654
00:36:48,998 --> 00:36:52,293
My whole career, my whole life
was like it never happened.

655
00:36:53,544 --> 00:36:56,547
Hulk is one of the biggest
legends in the history of this business.

656
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:58,007
That's undeniable.

657
00:36:59,091 --> 00:37:02,094
But I didn't fire Hulk Hogan.

658
00:37:04,805 --> 00:37:06,140
I fired Terry Bollea.

659
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:19,237
He was at such a low point.

660
00:37:22,907 --> 00:37:24,951
But he never told us about it

661
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:29,914
because he kind of separated himself
away from us too, you know?

662
00:37:33,709 --> 00:37:36,295
Everything in his life was falling apart.

663
00:37:41,509 --> 00:37:46,514
I had been through so many years
of craziness and drama and negativity.

664
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:51,394
For years, there was so much, "Woe is me."

665
00:37:51,477 --> 00:37:54,730
"Oh, woe is me, the world sucks,
life sucks, and then you die."

666
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:59,402
And then, uh, right when you think
you're done, the universe goes,

667
00:37:59,485 --> 00:38:03,406
"Here's something to be grateful for,"
that you didn't even expect.

668
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:11,122
I looked up,
and a whole queue had formed in the corner

669
00:38:11,205 --> 00:38:13,291
for people who wanted their picture taken.

670
00:38:13,374 --> 00:38:15,251
I was sitting there
with a girlfriend of mine.

671
00:38:15,334 --> 00:38:18,546
She said, "Hulk Hogan's over there.
We should go get a picture."

672
00:38:19,338 --> 00:38:23,009
And I said, "I'm not going to do that."

673
00:38:23,092 --> 00:38:25,428
I've lived in Clearwater
for almost my whole life,

674
00:38:25,511 --> 00:38:28,931
so he's been around, I just never met him.

675
00:38:29,015 --> 00:38:33,519
So I knew he was a wrestler,
and I knew that Clearwater loved him.

676
00:38:33,602 --> 00:38:35,104
That's what I knew.

677
00:38:36,314 --> 00:38:41,235
He looked up, and our eyes met,
and it was just like that zing.

678
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,696
And then he asked me on a date.

679
00:38:43,779 --> 00:38:45,990
I was just through my second divorce,

680
00:38:46,073 --> 00:38:48,409
and, uh, it was… it was a rough one.

681
00:38:49,493 --> 00:38:52,288
I'd speak out loud in my house,
"Why is this happening to me?"

682
00:38:52,371 --> 00:38:54,457
"Why is this still happening?"

683
00:38:54,540 --> 00:38:58,336
I fell asleep in my chair, and I heard,
"I'm putting you through a cleansing."

684
00:38:58,419 --> 00:39:01,088
I looked around,
there's nobody in the house,

685
00:39:01,172 --> 00:39:02,840
and I actually heard those words.

686
00:39:02,923 --> 00:39:06,135
So where they came from, or who said them,
you got me, but I heard them.

687
00:39:06,218 --> 00:39:08,512
He said he swore
he'd never date another blonde,

688
00:39:08,596 --> 00:39:11,599
and then he saw me. He goes, "Oh, no."

689
00:39:11,682 --> 00:39:14,060
He was just coming out of a divorce

690
00:39:14,143 --> 00:39:17,980
and healing from, I think,
his tenth back surgery at that time.

691
00:39:18,064 --> 00:39:20,900
You know, I was still, "Bah, humbug."

692
00:39:20,983 --> 00:39:22,651
You know, the "woe is me" crap.

693
00:39:22,735 --> 00:39:26,155
She goes,
"Are you just going to keep complaining?"

694
00:39:28,616 --> 00:39:30,826
"You're right. I'll shut up."

695
00:39:31,994 --> 00:39:35,039
"Are you going to be grateful
for the fact that we're here together,

696
00:39:35,122 --> 00:39:37,124
and this is such a beautiful day?"

697
00:39:38,667 --> 00:39:40,920
She invited me to go to church with her.

698
00:39:43,047 --> 00:39:44,882
I went to church with her,

699
00:39:44,965 --> 00:39:49,303
and, uh, actually listened
to what was being said.

700
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:52,139
You know, that He gave
His only begotten son,

701
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:54,892
that whoever believed in Him
shall have everlasting life,

702
00:39:54,975 --> 00:39:59,355
and I got hooked, baptized,
you know, born anew,

703
00:39:59,939 --> 00:40:02,274
forgiven for all of my sins.

704
00:40:02,358 --> 00:40:05,986
You know, and that was the beginning
of me starting my comeback.

705
00:40:07,363 --> 00:40:11,075
She's so dialed in with what's important
that it rubs off on me.

706
00:40:11,158 --> 00:40:13,577
Attitude is everything,
and everything is attitude.

707
00:40:13,661 --> 00:40:16,622
I should be thanking God
just to be alive every day.

708
00:40:17,748 --> 00:40:21,919
Some of these people have been waiting
40, 45 years to meet me.

709
00:40:22,002 --> 00:40:24,463
They've stuck with me
through thick and thin.

710
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:27,758
Whether I'm a good guy
or a bad guy in the wrestling business

711
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:32,388
or a good guy or a bad guy in real life,
they've stuck with me.

712
00:40:33,055 --> 00:40:34,682
Oh my God.

713
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:39,145
Look at all the kids
that stayed out of school today.

714
00:40:39,228 --> 00:40:41,272
You know what, brother? Do a U-turn.

715
00:40:41,355 --> 00:40:44,400
Hogan! Hogan! Hogan!

716
00:40:44,483 --> 00:40:45,484
Wow.

717
00:40:45,568 --> 00:40:48,070
-Can I get a selfie?
-We're rolling.

718
00:40:48,821 --> 00:40:52,324
I mean, there's two,
two realms that I have to exist in.

719
00:40:52,950 --> 00:40:54,702
There's the spiritual world,

720
00:40:54,785 --> 00:40:56,996
then this human incarnation
you keep one foot in.

721
00:40:57,079 --> 00:41:00,291
Terry Bollea was not
the greatest person all the time,

722
00:41:00,374 --> 00:41:02,877
and the character was impeccable,
even though I wasn't.

723
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,838
I just loved
the greatness of the character.

724
00:41:05,921 --> 00:41:10,342
I was ready to jump on
the Hulk Hogan train once again.

725
00:41:10,426 --> 00:41:13,095
Wow, what a good crew this is.

726
00:41:13,179 --> 00:41:17,933
-Time for the Hulkster. Thank you.
-All right, we got it, man.

727
00:41:18,017 --> 00:41:19,435
He's doing a lot better now.

728
00:41:19,518 --> 00:41:20,895
I'm just happy to be here.

729
00:41:20,978 --> 00:41:25,024
Hulk Hogan has been reinstated
into the WWE Hall of Fame.

730
00:41:25,107 --> 00:41:28,235
They invited me back to the WWE.

731
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:30,154
I feel like I'm home again.

732
00:41:30,237 --> 00:41:31,947
I feel like I'm still the champ.

733
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:33,699
Hulkamania running wild.

734
00:41:33,782 --> 00:41:37,161
And the Hulk Hogan brand is still alive.

735
00:41:37,244 --> 00:41:43,000
The immortal Hulk Hogan!

736
00:41:43,083 --> 00:41:46,670
Instead of going, sitting out,
and watching the sunset every night,

737
00:41:46,754 --> 00:41:49,548
and each year being a dog year,
making me seven years older,

738
00:41:49,632 --> 00:41:51,967
I decided, "Let me go back to work
and have some fun."

739
00:41:52,051 --> 00:41:54,094
-I'll get in here with you.
-Thanks, brother!

740
00:41:54,178 --> 00:41:56,764
-Hulk Hogan!
-All right, what's up?

741
00:42:00,267 --> 00:42:01,769
Brilliant.

742
00:42:01,852 --> 00:42:04,563
Hulk! Hey, Hulk Hogan.

743
00:42:04,647 --> 00:42:06,649
-Ready?
-Hulk Hogan!

744
00:42:06,732 --> 00:42:07,942
Love you too.

745
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:10,361
-How you doing? What's your name?
-My name's Lucas.

746
00:42:10,444 --> 00:42:12,321
Lucas, I knew I'd meet somebody special.

747
00:42:12,404 --> 00:42:14,657
Terry Bollea wasn't as good
as the character,

748
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:16,534
but the character helps people.

749
00:42:16,617 --> 00:42:20,037
In whatever way it helps them,
it helps them. That's all I know.

750
00:42:22,456 --> 00:42:25,000
-What's up, guys?
-Hogan!

751
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:28,379
How you doing?

752
00:42:29,004 --> 00:42:30,839
Without you, there's no wrestling.

753
00:42:30,923 --> 00:42:34,718
I, uh, I got remarried.
My wife has an 18-year-old autistic son.

754
00:42:34,802 --> 00:42:35,928
I fell in love with him.

755
00:42:36,011 --> 00:42:38,472
He can't do nothing but tell the truth.
I love it.

756
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:42,935
Hulk, um, would you like me
to have a picture with you?

757
00:42:43,018 --> 00:42:49,692
I wish you would take a picture with me
because that'll be history made.

758
00:42:49,775 --> 00:42:54,822
So I want to be that Hulk Hogan for them
that they expected to meet,

759
00:42:54,905 --> 00:42:57,575
whether it's when I was 30 or 90.

760
00:42:57,658 --> 00:43:00,119
-Nice to meet you, brother.
-He's got it, man.

761
00:43:00,202 --> 00:43:01,036
You're my hero.

762
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:02,997
Thank you, brother.
Very kind of you to say that.

763
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:05,457
I collect the merchandise of you.

764
00:43:06,041 --> 00:43:08,669
You know what?
As you're collecting that merchandise,

765
00:43:08,752 --> 00:43:10,588
I think your brother should pay for it.

766
00:43:10,671 --> 00:43:12,590
-Okay.
-Love you, man.

767
00:43:13,257 --> 00:43:16,385
I really was here for a reason
more than just wrestling.

768
00:43:16,468 --> 00:43:19,221
Something's going on here
that I haven't figured out yet,

769
00:43:19,305 --> 00:43:22,099
but something,
something really big is going to happen.

770
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:27,021
Yeah. There's a shot in here
of, uh, you and Donald Trump.

771
00:43:27,104 --> 00:43:30,357
Staying out of politics
has always been as a businessman,

772
00:43:30,441 --> 00:43:34,028
because my Hulkamaniacs have always
been Democrats and Republicans.

773
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:36,405
My arms aren't as big as his,
I'll tell you.

774
00:43:36,488 --> 00:43:38,866
You ever see anything like this?
It's amazing.

775
00:43:38,949 --> 00:43:40,826
So he wanted to stay out of politics,

776
00:43:40,909 --> 00:43:43,120
and when they'd ask him a question,

777
00:43:43,203 --> 00:43:46,373
because everything was about,
you know, politics, frankly,

778
00:43:46,457 --> 00:43:51,128
and he would be
sort of like neutral at best,

779
00:43:51,211 --> 00:43:53,047
and he wanted to be politically correct.

780
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:56,050
He doesn't want to lose fans and all that.
I understand that.

781
00:43:56,133 --> 00:43:57,885
Listen, baby, you… you do it.

782
00:43:57,968 --> 00:43:59,219
Okay, we'll give it a shot.

783
00:43:59,303 --> 00:44:02,139
You know, I met Donald Trump
back in the day, in the '80s.

784
00:44:02,222 --> 00:44:03,140
He's my friend.

785
00:44:03,223 --> 00:44:06,727
A lot of people would say I'm crazy,
but I know the person.

786
00:44:06,810 --> 00:44:08,228
I know him very well.

787
00:44:08,312 --> 00:44:11,523
I'm not saying
I agree with everything he does,

788
00:44:11,607 --> 00:44:16,153
but at least he's honest about who he is.

789
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:20,282
All right, just to be clear,
this is going to be a little bit of a zoo.

790
00:44:20,366 --> 00:44:23,619
2016, I was one
of the cowards that voted for Trump,

791
00:44:23,702 --> 00:44:25,329
but I wouldn't wear the red hat.

792
00:44:25,412 --> 00:44:27,665
It's an honor to be here,
I can tell you that.

793
00:44:27,748 --> 00:44:30,959
2020, I voted for Trump,
I was still the coward.

794
00:44:31,043 --> 00:44:34,380
Well, I was afraid to speak out.
I was really afraid to get into politics.

795
00:44:34,463 --> 00:44:38,050
And, uh, I think he regrets that.

796
00:44:39,551 --> 00:44:40,678
Perfect.

797
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:46,225
I was gonna vote for him this next time,
and I wanted to keep a low profile.

798
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:49,645
But they tried to kill Trump.

799
00:44:51,730 --> 00:44:53,148
Get down! Get down!

800
00:44:53,232 --> 00:44:56,485
When they tried to shoot him the other day
that did it for me, man.

801
00:44:56,568 --> 00:44:57,569
That…

802
00:44:58,529 --> 00:45:01,281
And I was done. I was pissed.

803
00:45:03,033 --> 00:45:07,121
I told my wife it might be a deal-breaker,
but it's something I have to do.

804
00:45:07,705 --> 00:45:09,581
Knowing that if I spoke out,

805
00:45:09,665 --> 00:45:14,211
that it could jeopardize everything
from my businesses to my life.

806
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:16,755
Coming forward for Trump,
as an entertainer,

807
00:45:16,839 --> 00:45:18,882
you divide your audience,

808
00:45:18,966 --> 00:45:21,260
and he was nervous about that.

809
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:25,097
Mike Johnson, Speaker of the House.
I've been a fan of you my whole life.

810
00:45:25,180 --> 00:45:26,974
Thanks for all the wonderful memories.

811
00:45:27,057 --> 00:45:29,226
-It was a lot of fun.
-Oh, man.

812
00:45:29,309 --> 00:45:32,438
The Hulk was always
very controversial, and that's okay.

813
00:45:32,521 --> 00:45:34,523
I'm fairly controversial.

814
00:45:34,606 --> 00:45:37,109
I think I've become less controversial
over the years,

815
00:45:37,192 --> 00:45:39,486
but I'm fairly controversial too.

816
00:45:39,570 --> 00:45:43,323
But I don't think Hulk cares about that,
and I don't care about that either.

817
00:45:43,407 --> 00:45:44,992
We're walking, here we go.

818
00:45:55,043 --> 00:46:01,842
USA, USA, USA, USA, USA!

819
00:46:01,925 --> 00:46:04,511
Well, let me tell you something, brother.

820
00:46:08,974 --> 00:46:10,350
You know something?

821
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:14,521
When I came here tonight,
there was so much energy in this room,

822
00:46:14,605 --> 00:46:17,524
I felt maybe
I was in Madison Square Garden

823
00:46:17,608 --> 00:46:19,526
getting ready to win another world title.

824
00:46:19,610 --> 00:46:22,029
Hulk Hogan!

825
00:46:25,324 --> 00:46:27,534
But what I found out was

826
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:31,371
I was in a room
full of real Americans, brother.

827
00:46:32,956 --> 00:46:36,502
And when they took a shot at my hero…

828
00:46:39,546 --> 00:46:44,843
…and they tried to kill
the next President of the United States,

829
00:46:45,552 --> 00:46:48,138
enough was enough!

830
00:46:48,222 --> 00:46:53,101
And I said,
let Trumpamania run wild, brother!

831
00:46:53,185 --> 00:46:58,065
USA! USA! USA! USA!

832
00:46:58,148 --> 00:47:00,484
He did the shirt ripping,
he did the whole thing,

833
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:01,819
and the place went crazy.

834
00:47:02,611 --> 00:47:05,781
I heard 20,000 people just explode.

835
00:47:09,618 --> 00:47:11,203
Yeah. It felt good, man.

836
00:47:11,286 --> 00:47:16,542
USA! USA! USA! USA!

837
00:47:16,625 --> 00:47:20,003
Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk! Hulk!

838
00:47:23,465 --> 00:47:25,092
Hulk! Hulk! Hulk!

839
00:47:25,175 --> 00:47:29,304
He tore his shirt off,
just like it was 1985 all over again,

840
00:47:29,388 --> 00:47:33,976
and I'm sure having that crowd go wild
probably felt like old times.

841
00:47:34,059 --> 00:47:39,106
What you gonna do when Donald Trump
and all the Trumpamaniacs

842
00:47:39,189 --> 00:47:41,817
run wild on you, brother?

843
00:47:51,285 --> 00:47:53,537
Hulk, it's your
all-time favorite president,

844
00:47:53,620 --> 00:47:57,875
and I just want to tell you,
you were unbelievable at the convention,

845
00:47:57,958 --> 00:47:59,710
uh, like, the talk of the town.

846
00:47:59,793 --> 00:48:02,504
And we had, by the way,
I don't know if you heard,

847
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:05,507
the biggest ratings they ever had
for any of these things by far.

848
00:48:05,591 --> 00:48:08,886
Fox had the biggest ratings
they've ever had,

849
00:48:08,969 --> 00:48:10,512
and you were the star.

850
00:48:10,596 --> 00:48:13,181
Nobody could do
what you did and entertain.

851
00:48:13,265 --> 00:48:15,517
And, uh, we love having you on our side.

852
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:18,604
You're a winner, man.
You're a champ and a winner.

853
00:48:18,687 --> 00:48:21,064
And I think it was
really good for you too.

854
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:23,525
I have to tell you,
everyone was really impressed.

855
00:48:23,609 --> 00:48:25,944
Take care of yourself. Thanks. Bye.

856
00:48:31,325 --> 00:48:34,286
Yes, sir. America's back.
We got our country back.

857
00:48:35,954 --> 00:48:37,039
How you guys doing?

858
00:48:37,122 --> 00:48:38,457
How you doing, sir?

859
00:48:38,540 --> 00:48:39,666
Okay, man.

860
00:48:39,750 --> 00:48:41,501
For wrestling fans like me,

861
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:45,964
it was like, Hulk Hogan should be
bigger than politics, right?

862
00:48:46,048 --> 00:48:48,842
I mean, like,
Superman is bigger than politics, right?

863
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:51,178
Because now he's just politics.

864
00:48:51,261 --> 00:48:53,472
Uh-oh. There you go, big man.

865
00:48:53,555 --> 00:48:55,265
Hulkster,
I could not appreciate you enough

866
00:48:55,349 --> 00:48:57,184
for what you did for Trump too. Thank you.

867
00:48:57,267 --> 00:48:59,519
-We got him in, didn't we?
-Got him in, brother.

868
00:48:59,603 --> 00:49:01,188
In this new chapter of his life,

869
00:49:01,271 --> 00:49:04,232
he wanted to be as authentic
and true to himself,

870
00:49:04,316 --> 00:49:06,109
not just the Hulk Hogan character.

871
00:49:06,193 --> 00:49:08,737
And, you know,
it wasn't without some backlash.

872
00:49:08,820 --> 00:49:10,822
We did get death-threat letters,

873
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:16,745
but, you know, for the overall, uh,
pro-America brand, it was… It was great.

874
00:49:16,828 --> 00:49:20,832
Oh!

875
00:49:20,916 --> 00:49:26,922
I cannot believe, after 45 years,
all you Hulkamaniacs are still with me.

876
00:49:30,842 --> 00:49:34,471
And I hate to go there,
but we got our country back. Thank God.

877
00:49:36,348 --> 00:49:39,434
USA! USA! USA!

878
00:49:39,518 --> 00:49:44,523
So if anybody here
wants one free, real American beer,

879
00:49:44,606 --> 00:49:48,193
give me a Hacksaw Jim Duggan hello!

880
00:49:48,276 --> 00:49:50,821
Hello!

881
00:49:50,904 --> 00:49:53,156
They said,
"You can't put your picture on the can."

882
00:49:53,240 --> 00:49:54,199
"Nobody does that."

883
00:49:54,282 --> 00:49:57,911
"George Clooney doesn't do it."
I said, "BS. Watch me."

884
00:49:59,121 --> 00:50:01,331
-Love you.
-Love you too. Thanks for coming.

885
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:04,292
Great speech at the RNC… I cried.

886
00:50:04,376 --> 00:50:06,128
Thank God he won, or I'd be in prison.

887
00:50:06,211 --> 00:50:07,546
Ah, me too.

888
00:50:07,629 --> 00:50:10,173
We love Hogan!

889
00:50:12,175 --> 00:50:15,303
50% of the population
is on the other side.

890
00:50:15,387 --> 00:50:18,849
I… I don't believe
in discussing politics and religion.

891
00:50:19,433 --> 00:50:21,935
You keep
your political beliefs to yourself,

892
00:50:22,519 --> 00:50:27,065
or you alienate 50% of your audience
right off the bat.

893
00:50:27,149 --> 00:50:28,900
Let's see this place.

894
00:50:31,820 --> 00:50:35,157
-So here's the entrance, here.
-Yeah.

895
00:50:36,199 --> 00:50:38,744
So, as you look behind you, all people.

896
00:50:38,827 --> 00:50:41,705
Brother, how you doing? Good, good, good.

897
00:50:41,788 --> 00:50:44,708
Netflix was sort
of a coming-out party for us.

898
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:48,128
We had just signed a monumental deal
to be on that platform,

899
00:50:48,211 --> 00:50:53,675
so we wanted to blend past,
present, and future of WWE.

900
00:50:54,176 --> 00:50:55,010
Wow.

901
00:50:55,093 --> 00:50:58,638
It was important
to see people like Hogan there.

902
00:50:58,722 --> 00:51:01,892
Welcome to Monday Night Raw!

903
00:51:04,227 --> 00:51:07,314
Go to sleep, CM Punk!

904
00:51:07,397 --> 00:51:13,403
Well, The Rock has come back
to Los Angeles!

905
00:51:15,822 --> 00:51:17,532
It's a special night.

906
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:21,078
Monday Night Raw in LA,

907
00:51:22,412 --> 00:51:23,955
Netflix premiere.

908
00:51:26,541 --> 00:51:29,044
I was very stoked to see Hulk Hogan,

909
00:51:29,127 --> 00:51:32,005
and he gave me a giant duffel bag
of the beer.

910
00:51:33,507 --> 00:51:35,425
It stung a little to… to feel

911
00:51:35,509 --> 00:51:38,970
that he wasn't as well-received
as, uh, previously.

912
00:51:46,019 --> 00:51:50,065
When it comes crashing down
And it hurts inside…

913
00:52:17,801 --> 00:52:20,929
Well, let me tell you something, brother.

914
00:52:24,558 --> 00:52:25,600
I was backstage,

915
00:52:25,684 --> 00:52:28,478
like, "Holy shit, Hogan's getting booed
out of the building."

916
00:52:28,562 --> 00:52:31,231
Did I think he was going to get booed
out of the building?

917
00:52:31,815 --> 00:52:35,235
Probably. Especially in LA.

918
00:52:35,318 --> 00:52:39,656
Right? There's a different vibe there
and a different mentality there.

919
00:52:45,871 --> 00:52:47,622
You know something, maniacs?

920
00:52:47,706 --> 00:52:51,585
I've been in this business
for over 40 years.

921
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:54,754
I said, "Jimmy Hart, did you hear?"

922
00:52:54,838 --> 00:52:56,756
"No, they didn't boo you."
I said, "Jimmy."

923
00:52:59,801 --> 00:53:01,970
The people booed me like crazy.

924
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:09,311
I could have LA hate me if I went
on Jesse Watters three times a week.

925
00:53:09,394 --> 00:53:11,229
Get your Trump pump on, everybody.

926
00:53:11,313 --> 00:53:13,565
Great to see you, Hulk.
We'll see you at the ball.

927
00:53:13,648 --> 00:53:16,776
This is politics.
Don't hate the player, hate the game.

928
00:53:17,652 --> 00:53:19,404
We're going to a damn blue state.

929
00:53:19,487 --> 00:53:23,116
I went, "Okay,
I'll let it ride, 'cause he's Hulk Hogan."

930
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:26,036
People were saying,
"Because of his affiliation with Trump."

931
00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:28,455
But I don't know, I felt like I knew why.

932
00:53:28,538 --> 00:53:30,248
He's made a lot of mistakes.

933
00:53:30,332 --> 00:53:31,958
For some people,

934
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:37,380
he hasn't necessarily
always atoned for those mistakes,

935
00:53:37,464 --> 00:53:40,550
or even the apologies were seen as hollow.

936
00:53:40,634 --> 00:53:45,847
So many people couldn't look past that,
and he's just got a polarizing presence.

937
00:53:45,931 --> 00:53:49,017
Those people were waiting
on Hulk Hogan to come out

938
00:53:49,100 --> 00:53:51,937
and make any kind of statement,

939
00:53:52,020 --> 00:53:55,357
just so they could let him know
how they really feel about him.

940
00:53:55,440 --> 00:53:57,192
That night, too much

941
00:53:57,275 --> 00:54:03,073
of the artist has been exposed
for them to perhaps cheer.

942
00:54:04,032 --> 00:54:06,826
Who knows what the truth really is?
Here's all I know.

943
00:54:06,910 --> 00:54:08,745
You know, I knew it bothered him.

944
00:54:13,375 --> 00:54:17,087
Do you want to go out being cheered
or being booed? Be cheered, of course.

945
00:54:17,170 --> 00:54:20,048
You had to feel
a little sad about that, right?

946
00:54:20,131 --> 00:54:21,716
-No, brother.
-No?

947
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:24,678
No, man. When I saw how intense
they were coming at me,

948
00:54:24,761 --> 00:54:27,264
if they had a knife,
they would've stuck me in the neck.

949
00:54:27,347 --> 00:54:30,475
So am I upset by that? Are you kidding me?

950
00:54:30,558 --> 00:54:33,103
Brother, it's completely opposite
of what you think.

951
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:39,317
Bro, I could come back as a bad guy in LA
and sell out that building with anybody.

952
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:40,527
And as crippled as I am,

953
00:54:40,610 --> 00:54:42,988
they'd love to see
my crippled ass get in that ring

954
00:54:43,071 --> 00:54:44,990
and get strapped and beaten and punched,

955
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:47,617
and cut my head off
and bleed like a pig for them.

956
00:54:47,701 --> 00:54:51,454
That red will turn to green instantly.
And they would love it.

957
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:53,873
If you're getting booed
'cause that's your job,

958
00:54:53,957 --> 00:54:56,960
and that's your role as an antagonist,

959
00:54:57,752 --> 00:54:59,004
please, boo me more.

960
00:55:00,213 --> 00:55:03,383
But if your job
is to go out there as the good guy,

961
00:55:03,466 --> 00:55:07,470
and you're not getting the reaction,
that's a different story, of course.

962
00:55:07,554 --> 00:55:10,640
I used to go to LA,
and they'd cheer me out of the building.

963
00:55:10,724 --> 00:55:11,850
Let's go, brother.

964
00:55:11,933 --> 00:55:13,977
Man, how's everybody doing?

965
00:55:15,312 --> 00:55:16,396
Holy smokes.

966
00:55:16,479 --> 00:55:20,317
-How's it feel to see the Garden?
-hold on, hold on, hold on, whoa.

967
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:24,154
But then I go to New York,
and people just cheer me everywhere I go.

968
00:55:24,237 --> 00:55:25,238
Hulkamania!

969
00:55:25,322 --> 00:55:27,699
-Running wild, brother.
-Let's go!

970
00:55:27,782 --> 00:55:29,909
Not everyone in your life
is going to love you.

971
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:31,953
You'll have people that don't like you.

972
00:55:32,037 --> 00:55:34,039
You know, there's no winning.

973
00:55:34,914 --> 00:55:38,835
Was there a difference
when you get cheered versus the booing?

974
00:55:38,918 --> 00:55:41,379
Yeah, of course, of course.

975
00:55:43,089 --> 00:55:44,549
Come on, Hulk!

976
00:55:44,632 --> 00:55:47,927
In all my glory,
when Hulkamania was running wild,

977
00:55:49,012 --> 00:55:50,263
the crowd was magic,

978
00:55:50,347 --> 00:55:53,308
the energy would just drag you up
out of any hole.

979
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:56,394
I saw Bruno Sammartino.
I've seen Elvis Presley in there.

980
00:55:56,478 --> 00:55:57,937
Nobody bigger than you, Hulk.

981
00:55:58,521 --> 00:56:04,277
As soon as I hit that ring,
it was just the end-all, be-all, you know?

982
00:56:04,361 --> 00:56:06,321
Where nothing else in the world matters

983
00:56:06,404 --> 00:56:09,866
except that present moment
that you're in the ring.

984
00:56:13,703 --> 00:56:16,039
When I went in that ring, I was not Terry.

985
00:56:16,122 --> 00:56:20,418
When I went in that ring, brother,
I was Hulk Hogan. I believed it.

986
00:56:20,502 --> 00:56:22,045
It's just magic.

987
00:56:23,254 --> 00:56:25,965
The Hulk seems to get stronger.

988
00:56:26,049 --> 00:56:27,926
That's why I fell in love with wrestling.

989
00:56:28,009 --> 00:56:29,552
Can't understand this.

990
00:56:29,636 --> 00:56:33,848
How is this man still standing
and fighting back?

991
00:56:34,808 --> 00:56:36,267
Once you plug in,

992
00:56:36,351 --> 00:56:38,937
you're in that moment
where there's a flow.

993
00:56:40,522 --> 00:56:45,443
The flow gets stronger and stronger,
and there's just like this crazy tsunami.

994
00:56:48,988 --> 00:56:55,537
It's just this crazy flow
of just being there,

995
00:56:56,329 --> 00:56:58,623
catching the right wave,

996
00:57:00,166 --> 00:57:03,545
and just staying in the pipeline
and never coming out of it,

997
00:57:03,628 --> 00:57:06,297
and just living and dying there.

998
00:57:06,381 --> 00:57:08,508
There's nothing else like it.

999
00:57:09,259 --> 00:57:11,970
I don't know how else to say it,
it's like you're coming all the time.

1000
00:57:21,980 --> 00:57:25,900
I always believed wrestling
was the most important thing there is.

1001
00:57:25,984 --> 00:57:27,902
It's immortality.

1002
00:57:30,989 --> 00:57:37,495
But I found out later that that's not
the gateway to eternal happiness.

1003
00:57:38,997 --> 00:57:42,459
Do you remember the time
when you were the happiest?

1004
00:57:43,042 --> 00:57:43,960
Yeah.

1005
00:57:44,544 --> 00:57:47,589
-Okay, here we are. You're holding him.
-Yeah.

1006
00:57:47,672 --> 00:57:50,467
-The Hulkster board.
-Yeah.

1007
00:57:50,550 --> 00:57:53,219
For a ride you'll never forget.

1008
00:57:53,303 --> 00:57:54,679
It's my baby.

1009
00:57:54,762 --> 00:57:59,976
Terry bought me my new minivan.
The hottest ride in town.

1010
00:58:00,059 --> 00:58:03,188
I mean,
I get really weird flashbacks, you know,

1011
00:58:03,271 --> 00:58:04,397
during the day.

1012
00:58:07,150 --> 00:58:13,281
Dad just got back
from his world tour, 1990, 11,000 miles.

1013
00:58:13,364 --> 00:58:15,950
Torn out.

1014
00:58:16,034 --> 00:58:19,829
And I'll be in the car by myself,
and I'll think of something, you know.

1015
00:58:19,913 --> 00:58:21,581
I'll catch myself smiling,

1016
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:23,791
like the village idiot,
by myself, you know?

1017
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:27,712
Because I'll think of something
real personal, and it'll make me smile.

1018
00:58:28,213 --> 00:58:29,839
You're like a big girl now.

1019
00:58:29,923 --> 00:58:31,591
Mommy, I spilled beer on my…

1020
00:58:31,674 --> 00:58:36,095
We love you very much,
Brooke, Nick, and Terry.

1021
00:58:36,179 --> 00:58:38,264
As far as this human incarnation goes,

1022
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:41,351
when I had both my kids,
they were very young.

1023
00:58:41,434 --> 00:58:43,603
Two babies.

1024
00:58:43,686 --> 00:58:46,064
-Two humongous babies.
-Two babies.

1025
00:58:46,147 --> 00:58:48,233
The young kids were really healthy.

1026
00:58:48,316 --> 00:58:49,400
Mama!

1027
00:58:49,484 --> 00:58:50,652
Here.

1028
00:58:51,277 --> 00:58:55,532
When Linda
was being the best mom I've ever seen.

1029
00:58:55,615 --> 00:59:00,954
And just being a great wife
and was steady as she goes.

1030
00:59:01,037 --> 00:59:03,456
Being the perfect mom
and the perfect friend…

1031
00:59:04,249 --> 00:59:07,794
-What a total ham bone.
-Ah!

1032
00:59:07,877 --> 00:59:11,005
…and the perfect soul mate
across the board,

1033
00:59:11,089 --> 00:59:16,261
that was probably, um,
the most happiest I've ever been.

1034
00:59:17,220 --> 00:59:20,139
Oh. Come out here. Come out here.

1035
00:59:20,723 --> 00:59:21,891
Look up in the sky.

1036
00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:23,101
-Daddy!
-I just…

1037
00:59:23,184 --> 00:59:25,228
-We just saw Santa!
-Dad!

1038
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:27,772
I just saw…I saw him banging at the back.

1039
00:59:27,855 --> 00:59:31,943
He took off back over the ocean.
Oh my God, look, he was here!

1040
00:59:32,026 --> 00:59:34,571
-And he was fat. And he had a big…
-Did you see him?

1041
00:59:34,654 --> 00:59:36,114
Pixie dust on this.

1042
00:59:36,197 --> 00:59:38,324
That's not pixie dust. It's reindeer dust.

1043
00:59:38,908 --> 00:59:40,535
When's Santa gonna bring my hair?

1044
00:59:55,883 --> 00:59:56,968
So we're done here?

1045
00:59:57,051 --> 00:59:58,720
I think we're good for today.

1046
00:59:58,803 --> 01:00:01,681
Maybe in a couple months,
we do this one more time.

1047
01:00:01,764 --> 01:00:02,599
Okay.

1048
01:00:04,559 --> 01:00:06,144
and we pick up little things we missed.

1049
01:00:06,227 --> 01:00:07,228
Okay.

1050
01:00:07,312 --> 01:00:09,731
But I think we got tons to start.

1051
01:00:12,817 --> 01:00:13,901
Oof.

1052
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:16,821
Man, it's hard to get up.

1053
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:40,011
We have some breaking news right now.

1054
01:00:40,094 --> 01:00:42,221
Wrestling legend Hulk Hogan died today

1055
01:00:42,305 --> 01:00:45,642
after suffering cardiac arrest
at his home in Clearwater, Florida.

1056
01:00:45,725 --> 01:00:48,102
Now to the death
of wrestling icon Hulk Hogan.

1057
01:00:48,186 --> 01:00:51,439
A man known the world over,
who defined the face of wrestling.

1058
01:00:51,522 --> 01:00:53,691
Hogan, whose real name was Terry Bollea…

1059
01:00:53,775 --> 01:00:56,486
Terry Bollea is widely recognized

1060
01:00:56,569 --> 01:00:59,405
as the biggest wrestling star of all time.

1061
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:01,908
-Greatest.
-Tributes are pouring in.

1062
01:01:01,991 --> 01:01:04,035
So many grew up knowing and watching him,

1063
01:01:04,118 --> 01:01:07,747
and then fans have been coming in
a steady stream all day taking pictures.

1064
01:01:07,830 --> 01:01:10,458
One of pop culture's
most recognizable figures.

1065
01:01:10,541 --> 01:01:12,251
A larger-than-life figure.

1066
01:01:12,335 --> 01:01:14,796
Gone in what seems like such a sudden way.

1067
01:01:14,879 --> 01:01:16,464
He died at the age of 71.

1068
01:01:16,547 --> 01:01:19,550
-He was 71 years old.
-Hogan was 71 years old.

1069
01:01:22,387 --> 01:01:24,389
I talked to Eric Bischoff.

1070
01:01:25,515 --> 01:01:31,729
Eric called me this morning at 11:30
and said, "Hey, man, uh…"

1071
01:01:32,522 --> 01:01:37,610
"I just heard Hulk may have a heart issue
and that he's gone to the hospital."

1072
01:01:39,237 --> 01:01:40,571
I hung up with him. I called Paul.

1073
01:01:41,239 --> 01:01:46,244
While on the phone with Paul,
Paul said, uh, "Hang on."

1074
01:01:46,327 --> 01:01:49,247
He says, "Oh my God…" Uh…

1075
01:01:50,957 --> 01:01:53,209
"They're reporting that Hulk died."

1076
01:01:57,588 --> 01:01:59,465
And it's just surreal.

1077
01:02:08,599 --> 01:02:12,687
Hulkster. Where… Where'd that come from?

1078
01:02:13,980 --> 01:02:16,107
Where the hell did that come from?

1079
01:02:18,276 --> 01:02:22,697
It signified the end of my era.

1080
01:02:23,698 --> 01:02:26,617
That it was now… The book was closed.

1081
01:02:26,701 --> 01:02:31,289
It… it… Hulk dying
made you feel real mortal.

1082
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:47,096
It's strange because there was
never a time where I was in his gym

1083
01:02:47,180 --> 01:02:48,306
working out without him.

1084
01:02:52,602 --> 01:02:55,563
But it's comforting in a way

1085
01:02:55,646 --> 01:02:58,816
to be around his weight equipment
and his gym.

1086
01:03:03,696 --> 01:03:06,699
And Nicholas
just wants nothing but his dad.

1087
01:03:07,241 --> 01:03:08,993
Only wants his dad.

1088
01:03:09,076 --> 01:03:10,703
A little bit of protein, son.

1089
01:03:14,290 --> 01:03:17,668
It was just tough to process all of it.

1090
01:03:19,337 --> 01:03:22,882
You know, everybody knows
he went in to have a neck surgery.

1091
01:03:24,467 --> 01:03:29,388
And, you know, after the neck surgery,
there were some complications.

1092
01:03:31,015 --> 01:03:34,435
This was the day
before Terry went in for neck surgery.

1093
01:03:34,519 --> 01:03:39,732
He's… You know, we're smiling.
He's bright-eyed, and, um…

1094
01:03:41,067 --> 01:03:43,486
we never got back to that spot again.

1095
01:03:44,737 --> 01:03:49,742
It was about two and a half months
that we were in and out of hospitals.

1096
01:03:50,535 --> 01:03:55,248
But he still showed so much resilience
and strength in those moments.

1097
01:03:56,749 --> 01:03:59,710
I wish we never did the neck surgery.

1098
01:04:04,423 --> 01:04:06,092
Oh.

1099
01:04:10,721 --> 01:04:13,891
The thing that I'll miss the most
is just being able to call him.

1100
01:04:13,975 --> 01:04:17,562
You know, it just feels weird
that I haven't talked to him.

1101
01:04:17,645 --> 01:04:21,858
I still cared about him the same.
It doesn't go away.

1102
01:04:21,941 --> 01:04:25,278
You know, I wish things
would have turned out differently for us.

1103
01:04:25,945 --> 01:04:29,574
-All right, yes! Stand up by yourself.
-What was your wish, Linda?

1104
01:04:29,657 --> 01:04:34,829
But then when he got sick,
I realized my love never faded for him.

1105
01:04:34,912 --> 01:04:36,372
I still had love for him.

1106
01:04:36,873 --> 01:04:39,333
I really do. I still love him.

1107
01:04:39,417 --> 01:04:40,626
It's my baby.

1108
01:04:42,587 --> 01:04:44,130
How you doing, cupcake?

1109
01:04:47,633 --> 01:04:50,761
You know, somebody
that was your partner for so long.

1110
01:04:50,845 --> 01:04:54,557
And then to just see him
suffering like that toward the end, um…

1111
01:04:55,558 --> 01:04:56,517
You know, to just know

1112
01:04:56,601 --> 01:04:59,353
that he really didn't deserve
to go out that way.

1113
01:04:59,437 --> 01:05:00,855
It's… It's sad.

1114
01:05:00,938 --> 01:05:03,149
You know, I'm sad for my kids.

1115
01:05:05,484 --> 01:05:07,862
In my eyes, he was always immortal.

1116
01:05:07,945 --> 01:05:11,198
The child in me always believed that.

1117
01:05:12,283 --> 01:05:15,620
This is his big old size-17 boot.

1118
01:05:16,412 --> 01:05:21,125
And for comparison, my shoe is a size 12.

1119
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:26,130
-Oh!
-Why are those feet on the table?

1120
01:05:27,506 --> 01:05:29,967
Just big feet.
You gonna eat your cake with those feet?

1121
01:05:47,193 --> 01:05:49,153
All right, guys, welcome to Cleveland.

1122
01:05:49,236 --> 01:05:52,490
Just before we get started,
as I'm sure everyone is aware,

1123
01:05:52,573 --> 01:05:57,954
unfortunate passing
of Hulk Hogan yesterday.

1124
01:05:59,121 --> 01:06:03,125
Hard to say there's been
a more influential figure,

1125
01:06:03,209 --> 01:06:05,586
especially on the performing side.

1126
01:06:05,670 --> 01:06:07,672
These are empty and ready to go?

1127
01:06:07,755 --> 01:06:09,799
No one is perfect in life.

1128
01:06:09,882 --> 01:06:11,509
And they had ups and downs.

1129
01:06:11,592 --> 01:06:14,512
But we're going to continue
to remember Hulk Hogan

1130
01:06:14,595 --> 01:06:16,597
as what he meant to this industry.

1131
01:06:17,556 --> 01:06:23,062
His influence cannot be denied
and it cannot be overstated.

1132
01:06:24,981 --> 01:06:28,734
You could make an argument
that we wouldn't be sitting here today.

1133
01:06:28,818 --> 01:06:31,195
This business might have gone
the way of roller derby

1134
01:06:31,278 --> 01:06:34,949
or some other shit
that didn't quite make it to the end.

1135
01:06:35,032 --> 01:06:36,659
But here we are.

1136
01:06:36,742 --> 01:06:39,078
So we're going to start
this show out tonight

1137
01:06:39,161 --> 01:06:41,497
with a ten-bell salute
with everybody on stage.

1138
01:06:42,665 --> 01:06:44,709
I don't think it needs to be said,

1139
01:06:44,792 --> 01:06:49,922
but anybody that has an issue,
does not want to be on that stage,

1140
01:06:50,006 --> 01:06:53,884
no problem, no issue, no… no anything.

1141
01:06:56,345 --> 01:06:59,640
I know it's complicated,
I do, how everyone feels,

1142
01:06:59,724 --> 01:07:04,562
but I think we all have to kind of wrestle
with the idea that he's gone.

1143
01:07:05,229 --> 01:07:09,984
And there's so many great things
about the immortal Hulk Hogan.

1144
01:07:10,067 --> 01:07:11,527
Can we focus on those?

1145
01:07:16,741 --> 01:07:18,034
It's just such a shock.

1146
01:07:18,117 --> 01:07:21,287
You know, Hulk and I have been friends
for over 40 years.

1147
01:07:21,370 --> 01:07:24,999
Everything that we've done together,
and all of a sudden, it's over.

1148
01:07:25,082 --> 01:07:27,001
I just couldn't believe it.

1149
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:31,839
And I still choke up, every now and then,
when I talk about it.

1150
01:07:31,922 --> 01:07:36,552
I know tonight, when we go on the stage
out here and do the ten-bell salute,

1151
01:07:36,635 --> 01:07:38,929
I know I'll break down again.

1152
01:07:39,013 --> 01:07:41,390
And this is the face of the Hulkster

1153
01:07:41,474 --> 01:07:44,643
that's going to represent
the whole country of America.

1154
01:07:46,729 --> 01:07:48,272
What a great night, Hulkster.

1155
01:07:48,355 --> 01:07:50,983
I know you're probably
looking upstairs, man.

1156
01:07:51,067 --> 01:07:52,860
What a great night for you.

1157
01:07:54,779 --> 01:07:56,781
I know I'm gonna be very sad.

1158
01:07:56,864 --> 01:07:59,408
It's like being at a place

1159
01:07:59,492 --> 01:08:02,745
where I know my friend wants to be here
with us doing this tonight,

1160
01:08:02,828 --> 01:08:04,038
and he won't be.

1161
01:08:05,289 --> 01:08:07,833
And I know he's up there now
looking down tonight,

1162
01:08:07,917 --> 01:08:09,460
but he's with all of his friends.

1163
01:08:09,543 --> 01:08:12,046
His friends are down here,
and his friends are up there, Brian.

1164
01:08:12,630 --> 01:08:16,884
He's going to see Dusty Rhodes.
He's going to see André the Giant.

1165
01:08:16,967 --> 01:08:18,636
The Iron Sheik.

1166
01:08:18,719 --> 01:08:23,933
He's going to see Randy Savage,
Rowdy Roddy Piper, Mean Gene Okerlund.

1167
01:08:25,017 --> 01:08:27,269
Maybe you can go into the ring
once more up there,

1168
